  "description": "<i>Heritage</i> is an arcade adventure game inspired by <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Artefakt+Przodkow\">Artefakt Przodków</a>, released back in 1992 for Atari 8-bit platform. As a space pilot sent on a dangerous mission, the player must visit an asteroid - former shelter of mad Myriadians scientists - to recover their inventions preserved on disks containing scientific data. As the spacecraft was destroyed during landing on the planet, the mission is complicated by the necessity of finding the spare parts.<br><br>There are many useful objects scattered around the space base and its surroundings. The pilot may carry two items at a time. Same limit applies also in each location, where only two things may be dropped on the ground. Apart from using items the player may read notes and use Jetpack with unlimited fuel, especially needed to avoid robots and other hostile creatures. <br><br><br><br>",
